WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.440
So today with us is Wolfgang Smith.

00:03.440 --> 00:09.280
He has majors in physics, mathematics, and philosophy.

00:09.280 --> 00:11.320
He contributed a theoretical solution

00:11.320 --> 00:13.680
to the reentry problem for spaceflight

00:13.680 --> 00:16.000
during his work as an aerodynamicist.

00:16.000 --> 00:17.520
He has a doctorate in mathematics

00:17.520 --> 00:19.160
and pursued a career as a mathematician

00:19.160 --> 00:22.320
until his retirement in 1992.

00:22.320 --> 00:24.560
He devoted himself to the publication of books,

00:24.560 --> 00:26.920
mission to correct the fallacies of contemporary

00:27.880 --> 00:30.360
scientific belief, by the way, of insights derived

00:30.360 --> 00:32.960
from the perennial wisdom of mankind.

00:32.960 --> 00:36.440
These works focus primarily on foundational problems

00:36.440 --> 00:39.600
in quantum theory and the problems of visual perception.

00:39.600 --> 00:42.840
Welcome, Wolfgang.

00:42.840 --> 00:44.000
Well, thank you.

00:44.000 --> 00:46.120
Glad to be here.

00:46.120 --> 00:47.720
Very, very glad you're here.

00:47.720 --> 00:49.120
Very excited.

00:49.120 --> 00:51.440
With us also today is Brian Murphy.

00:51.440 --> 00:54.320
Now, Brian, could you please introduce yourself

00:54.320 --> 00:57.200
while you're here?

00:57.200 --> 00:57.720
Hi, Jack.

00:57.720 --> 00:59.920
Thank you and hello to your audience.

00:59.920 --> 01:01.600
I'll make my comments brief, and then

01:01.600 --> 01:03.280
I'll turn it back to you and Wolfgang,

01:03.280 --> 01:06.320
because that's really where the money is in this conversation.

01:06.320 --> 01:09.920
And I came to know Wolfgang after seeing the documentary

01:09.920 --> 01:13.320
about him called The End of Quantum Reality.

01:13.320 --> 01:15.400
And after that, I ordered one of his books.

01:15.400 --> 01:17.880
In that case, it was Science and Myth

01:17.880 --> 01:21.320
with a response to Stephen Hawking's The Grand Design.

01:21.320 --> 01:23.480
And after reading that book, I reached out

01:23.480 --> 01:25.760
to the producer of the documentary on Facebook.

01:25.760 --> 01:28.080
And I asked him if he had thought about creating

01:28.080 --> 01:31.080
an educational initiative in the foundation.

01:31.080 --> 01:33.400
And that led to a conversation and introduction

01:33.400 --> 01:36.280
to Wolfgang and a friendship that has developed

01:36.280 --> 01:37.520
over the past three years.

01:37.520 --> 01:40.320
So we're now developing educational outreach

01:40.320 --> 01:42.720
and hopefully a lecture series under the banner

01:42.720 --> 01:44.240
of Project Scola.

01:44.240 --> 01:47.600
And we have a number of prominent and highly skilled

01:47.600 --> 01:49.840
and educated scholars from around the world who

01:49.840 --> 01:52.680
are committed to this endeavor.

01:52.680 --> 01:54.640
And so I have to say, when I read that book,

01:54.640 --> 01:56.440
and I mean in the first chapter of that book,

01:56.440 --> 01:58.840
the entire edifice of the worldview

01:58.840 --> 02:01.600
that I had imbibed over the many years

02:01.600 --> 02:03.680
just sort of melted into oblivion.

02:03.680 --> 02:06.680
And I think we're all familiar with that worldview.

02:06.680 --> 02:09.720
It's the one that purports to be scientific.

02:09.720 --> 02:12.440
It generally comes from PhDs who tell us

02:12.440 --> 02:15.760
we're sums of parts or composed of atoms or particles

02:15.760 --> 02:18.720
speeding through space and time to no purpose.

02:18.720 --> 02:21.600
And some might even say we have no free will

02:21.720 --> 02:23.760
or that our actions and decisions

02:23.760 --> 02:26.960
are determined in advance by these forces of physics.

02:26.960 --> 02:29.560
And so, but I'm like one of your audience members.

02:29.560 --> 02:30.440
I'm a lay person.

02:30.440 --> 02:31.640
I don't have a PhD.

02:31.640 --> 02:33.000
I'm not a physicist.

02:33.000 --> 02:34.440
But I'm very interested in this topic

02:34.440 --> 02:37.600
because I think it goes to the very heart of reality.

02:37.600 --> 02:40.280
It goes to the very heart of what it means to be human.

02:40.280 --> 02:42.160
And so in Wolfgang's latest book,

02:42.160 --> 02:44.240
Physics, A Science and Quest of Ontology,

02:44.240 --> 02:46.000
which you're gonna talk to him about,

02:46.000 --> 02:48.800
Wolfgang really offers a new cosmology,

02:48.800 --> 02:50.600
which is really an ancient cosmology.

02:50.600 --> 02:53.960
And I think it'll really open people's eyes

02:53.960 --> 02:55.600
to things they haven't heard before

02:55.600 --> 02:56.880
or maybe haven't heard in decades.

02:56.880 --> 02:59.520
So the bottom line is what I want your audience to know

02:59.520 --> 03:03.160
is that Wolfgang Smith is not just another guy

03:03.160 --> 03:05.720
with some interesting ideas among many.

03:05.720 --> 03:09.640
No, I really feel there's no one like Wolfgang Smith.

03:09.640 --> 03:13.520
And he has resolved the quantum reality problem,

03:13.520 --> 03:14.880
the measurement problem.

03:14.880 --> 03:17.840
And what he shows with amazing simplicity

03:17.840 --> 03:22.240
is that our world is full of irreducible holes

03:22.240 --> 03:24.560
of beings imbued with qualities

03:24.560 --> 03:26.160
that transcend the world of physics.

03:26.160 --> 03:30.120
And so like Plato's analogy of the cave,

03:30.120 --> 03:33.200
he invites his readers and he invites listeners

03:33.200 --> 03:35.320
to make that ascent out of the cave.

03:35.320 --> 03:38.160
So I would invite you to listen to this man

03:38.160 --> 03:40.400
and become a member of his foundation,

03:40.400 --> 03:41.840
the Philosophia Initiative.

03:41.840 --> 03:44.040
And with that, I'll turn it back to you too.

03:45.040 --> 03:45.960
Thank you.

03:45.960 --> 03:47.280
That was a great introduction.

03:47.280 --> 03:48.760
Thank you.

03:48.760 --> 03:51.240
Probably much better than I would have done.

03:51.240 --> 03:56.400
Now, as I said just before we were in life,

03:56.400 --> 03:58.280
Wolfgang kind of flew under the radar for me.

03:58.280 --> 03:59.760
It kind of surprised me.

03:59.760 --> 04:04.600
I got an email from his publicist and I had to check him out.

04:04.600 --> 04:06.520
And they sent me a book.

04:06.520 --> 04:11.320
This is Physics Assigned in Quest of Nontology.

04:11.320 --> 04:13.760
And it was actually much more interesting

04:13.760 --> 04:15.880
than I initially expected, Wolfgang.

04:15.880 --> 04:18.840
You have a beautiful way of writing, honestly.

04:18.840 --> 04:20.600
But I'm not bad.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.120
But you also take no prisoners.

04:22.120 --> 04:25.560
And I kind of like that.

04:25.560 --> 04:27.320
Let me give you one example here.

04:27.320 --> 04:29.320
And you said, I came upon the words,

04:29.320 --> 04:32.080
there is no way to convince an expert that he or she has

04:32.080 --> 04:34.400
done nonsense for 30 years.

04:34.400 --> 04:38.120
I realized instantly that this person has something to say.

04:38.120 --> 04:40.400
When I read that, I instantly realized

04:40.400 --> 04:42.480
that Wolfgang has something to say to.

04:42.480 --> 04:50.600
So it was kind of tongue-in-cheek, but I like it.

04:50.600 --> 04:53.880
Well, the people who are listening right now

04:53.880 --> 05:01.160
are from the idealist space, metaphysical idealism.

05:01.160 --> 05:07.520
So we're already not really convinced of scientism.

05:07.520 --> 05:09.880
But it doesn't mean that we have to talk about idealism.

05:09.880 --> 05:12.240
But there's this little thing about,

05:12.240 --> 05:15.320
I haven't read, I haven't come across this in this book.

05:15.320 --> 05:17.640
So before we start, I'm actually kind of curious.

05:17.640 --> 05:22.080
Just what are your thoughts on just consciousness?

05:22.080 --> 05:23.720
I haven't seen the word in this book.

05:23.720 --> 05:26.920
Maybe if you wrote about it, maybe you haven't.

05:26.920 --> 05:30.760
But physicists have a lot to say about consciousness.

05:30.760 --> 05:33.840
And idealists have a lot to say about consciousness.

05:33.840 --> 05:37.120
But I haven't heard Wolfgang say anything about consciousness.

05:37.120 --> 05:39.520
Is there anything you'd like to personally

05:39.520 --> 05:44.160
or professionally say about that topic?

05:44.160 --> 05:49.160
Well, I think the topic of consciousness

05:49.160 --> 05:54.520
is obviously very central, very major.

05:54.520 --> 05:58.960
And what I have to say about it, I think,

05:58.960 --> 06:06.320
can best be described as being the very opposite of what

06:06.320 --> 06:14.920
is nowadays involved regarding the subject of consciousness.

06:14.920 --> 06:25.480
Because I am persuaded that instead of coming somehow

06:25.480 --> 06:32.920
up from the bottom by some process of evolution,

06:32.920 --> 06:37.080
consciousness is ultimately, in the final count,

06:37.080 --> 06:41.280
what used to be called a Norman day.

06:41.280 --> 06:46.520
It is actually rooted in divinity itself.

06:46.520 --> 06:51.680
And by way of explication, let me mention

06:51.680 --> 06:58.400
that the oldest tradition, intellectual tradition

06:58.400 --> 07:02.040
in the world unquestionably is a Vedic.

07:02.040 --> 07:05.920
And in the Vedic tradition, consciousness

07:05.920 --> 07:08.840
is indeed a Norman day.

07:08.840 --> 07:16.400
And it is part of the Sanskrit word satchitananda.

07:16.400 --> 07:23.400
So satchitananda, these are three words put into one.

07:23.400 --> 07:26.560
Sat means being.

07:26.560 --> 07:29.920
Chit means consciousness.

07:29.920 --> 07:33.400
And ananda means bliss.

07:33.400 --> 07:40.120
So being consciousness and bliss are, so to speak,

07:40.120 --> 07:44.160
the three aspects or faces, if you will,

07:44.160 --> 07:48.320
of the divinity, the very, very first principle.

07:48.320 --> 07:55.160
And I honestly believe that there is no other way

07:55.160 --> 07:58.120
of really understanding consciousness.

07:58.120 --> 08:00.000
It's not an epiphenomenon.

08:00.000 --> 08:04.960
It has nothing whatsoever to do with neurons.

08:04.960 --> 08:09.960
And in fact, it is rooted in the very, very first principle

08:09.960 --> 08:11.720
of all, which is God.

08:14.360 --> 08:21.760
So I think these remarks may suffice

08:21.760 --> 08:27.920
to show that my thinking is really very far removed

08:27.920 --> 08:32.400
from the contemporary, because the contemporary thinking

08:32.400 --> 08:36.680
is characterized by the fact that almost instinctively,

08:36.680 --> 08:42.440
contemporary Western man wants to understand everything

08:42.440 --> 08:48.560
from the bottom, which he conceives more or less

08:48.560 --> 08:52.880
in terms of quantum mechanics.

08:52.880 --> 08:59.280
And this is, to me, the epitome of error.

08:59.280 --> 09:04.000
And in fact, I would justify this claim

09:04.000 --> 09:12.600
by pointing out that the contemporary metaphysics is

09:12.600 --> 09:17.200
really nothing new, but it is a revival

09:17.240 --> 09:23.360
of the philosophy of Democritus, who famously

09:23.360 --> 09:37.600
said the Golger believed in qualities, color,

09:37.600 --> 09:40.320
the sweet and the bitter.

09:40.320 --> 09:45.920
But in reality, there is only atoms and the void.

09:45.960 --> 09:54.440
So this is basically not only one

09:54.440 --> 09:58.560
of the oldest philosophical positions of mankind,

09:58.560 --> 10:03.520
but it has been revived in the 17th century,

10:03.520 --> 10:08.520
and it has become our modern cradle.

10:08.520 --> 10:14.480
And let me mention that very soon after Democritus

10:14.480 --> 10:21.200
propounded his theory concerning atoms and the void,

10:21.200 --> 10:29.840
Plato attacked it, and I believe rigorously disqualified

10:29.840 --> 10:33.440
this position once and for all.

10:33.440 --> 10:37.960
And so for 2,000 years thereafter,

10:37.960 --> 10:45.800
the well-informed regarded this atomistic metaphysics

10:45.800 --> 10:47.760
as a heresy.

10:47.760 --> 10:52.080
And so what happened in the 17th century

10:52.080 --> 10:58.640
under the aegis of people like Descartes and Galileo,

10:58.640 --> 11:05.880
that ancient heresy was revived and became

11:05.880 --> 11:12.320
the foundation of what we nowadays call the Enlightenment.

11:12.320 --> 11:21.720
So this is, so to speak, the historical overview of where

11:21.720 --> 11:25.400
we find ourselves today.

11:25.400 --> 11:31.920
And needless to say, I have been an opponent

11:31.920 --> 11:40.720
of the current Weltanschauung since the age of 14, really.

11:40.720 --> 11:43.800
Really, what happened when you were 14?

11:43.800 --> 11:46.680
That made that happen?

11:46.680 --> 11:51.960
Well, I think the decisive event was that somehow or other,

11:51.960 --> 11:56.600
I came across a very important book,

11:56.600 --> 12:02.160
a book by Alfred North Whitehead entitled

12:02.160 --> 12:05.520
Science in the Modern World.

12:05.520 --> 12:07.920
I read this book with great interest.

12:07.920 --> 12:15.040
I don't think I understood that much because I was very young.

12:15.040 --> 12:23.800
But I understood enough to be fascinated and, in a sense,

12:23.800 --> 12:30.720
to be devoted to these questions for the rest of my life.

12:34.200 --> 12:41.960
So Whitehead, as it were, awakened my philosophical interest

12:41.960 --> 12:47.000
and instincts, if you will, instinctively

12:47.000 --> 12:51.600
when I read about the fallacy of misplaced concreteness

12:51.600 --> 12:55.640
and these things, I realized that this must be true.

12:58.200 --> 13:05.560
And so this started me on a career which

13:05.560 --> 13:09.000
put me in the position of the outsider

13:09.000 --> 13:13.240
from the very beginning.

13:13.240 --> 13:16.240
I always felt myself as an outsider

13:16.240 --> 13:19.520
in the contemporary Western culture.

13:19.520 --> 13:24.280
And the reason was that I felt myself as an insider

13:24.280 --> 13:30.240
when it comes to the ancient philosophies, primarily

13:30.240 --> 13:32.720
Platonism.

13:32.720 --> 13:37.920
So in Platonism, I felt that I was an insider.

13:37.920 --> 13:39.960
Not that I understood it that well,

13:39.960 --> 13:44.000
but instinctively I was drawn to it.

13:44.080 --> 13:50.440
And something within me assured me

13:50.440 --> 13:53.720
that this must be the truth.

13:53.720 --> 14:00.400
And incidentally, Platonism doesn't stand alone.

14:00.400 --> 14:08.280
It is inherently the same as the Vedic tradition.

14:08.280 --> 14:11.160
There are certain differences.

14:11.160 --> 14:13.600
But in essence, it is the same doctrine.

14:16.160 --> 14:27.760
And as I said, the contemporary Weltanschauung,

14:27.760 --> 14:32.400
which is regards particles of some kind or another

14:32.400 --> 14:38.320
as a very basis from which everything else evolves,

14:38.320 --> 14:47.480
that Weltanschauung is really nothing new at all.

14:47.480 --> 14:50.680
As I said, it goes back to the Democritus.

14:50.680 --> 14:53.720
And you might say it is one of the oldest heresies

14:53.720 --> 14:56.520
in the history of human thought.

14:56.520 --> 14:58.800
You're not a fan of atomistic thinking.

14:58.800 --> 15:02.880
That's certainly what I got it from reading your book.

15:02.880 --> 15:09.080
And you even go as far as to say that there are no,

15:09.080 --> 15:10.560
that particles do not exist.

15:14.840 --> 15:23.280
Yes, when you really pursue the Platonist metaphysics

15:23.280 --> 15:32.440
and apply it to the contemporary panorama of physics

15:32.520 --> 15:35.720
with its division between classical physics and quantum

15:35.720 --> 15:44.200
physics, you find, and this came to me as an amazement,

15:44.200 --> 15:49.880
you find that everything falls into place.

15:49.880 --> 15:53.960
And you can, in fact, understand this division

15:53.960 --> 15:58.760
between classical physics and quantum physics

15:58.760 --> 16:05.080
in a brand new way, which finally makes sense.

16:05.080 --> 16:07.800
I really like you to go deeper into that,

16:07.800 --> 16:12.320
or at least explain your solution to this problem.

16:12.320 --> 16:16.240
So if you can briefly state the problem,

16:16.240 --> 16:17.320
and then your solution.

16:21.560 --> 16:27.480
Yes, let me just say by way of introduction

16:27.480 --> 16:33.680
that the Platonist metaphysics is, in a sense,

16:33.680 --> 16:41.400
the diametric opposite of what contemporary intellectuals

16:41.400 --> 16:47.080
believe, because contemporary intellectuals

16:47.080 --> 16:52.440
believe that it all begins with atoms.

16:53.440 --> 17:00.840
Nowadays, this is conceived evidently in quantum mechanical terms,

17:00.840 --> 17:07.240
but metaphysically speaking, it's just atoms and the void,

17:07.240 --> 17:12.840
very much as the democratus conceived of it.

17:12.840 --> 17:18.240
It's the beginning of the fifth century BC.

17:19.240 --> 17:25.520
So in a sense, you can say there's nothing new under the sun,

17:25.520 --> 17:31.400
because stripped of its technical aspects,

17:31.400 --> 17:37.280
the contemporary worldview is basically

17:37.280 --> 17:40.160
democratus all over again.

17:40.200 --> 17:49.800
And it is as much a heresy today as it was in the early days

17:49.800 --> 17:51.640
of democratus.

17:51.640 --> 17:57.200
In other words, it is simply false to say

17:57.200 --> 18:03.760
that everything arises from particles.

18:03.760 --> 18:08.800
There's no evidence to that effect.

18:08.800 --> 18:12.600
People may think so, but if you dig into it a little bit more

18:12.600 --> 18:20.160
deeply, you find that all these purported scenarios really

18:20.160 --> 18:23.560
prove to be baseless.

18:23.560 --> 18:30.600
And if you go into it with any kind of mathematical depths,

18:30.600 --> 18:37.800
you find quickly enough that this contemporary scenario, which

18:37.800 --> 18:44.440
tries to reduce everything to aggregates of particles,

18:44.440 --> 18:48.280
actually proves to be impossible.

18:48.280 --> 18:53.400
And in fact, it may interest many people

18:53.400 --> 19:02.200
to know that starting in the year 1998,

19:02.200 --> 19:07.160
this philosophy, this Belt and Schoen,

19:07.160 --> 19:09.680
has really been disproved.

19:09.680 --> 19:14.240
It turns out to be mathematically impossible.

19:14.240 --> 19:19.240
And it is very simple.

19:19.240 --> 19:22.320
I think I can explain that in a few words,

19:22.320 --> 19:25.640
comprehensible to the non-specialists.

19:25.640 --> 19:40.280
If you start out with particles, then you need to talk about evolution.

19:40.280 --> 19:45.440
You need to introduce this term, because somehow these particles

19:45.440 --> 19:49.320
have to give rise to all that there is,

19:49.320 --> 20:01.760
beginning with the planetary system and the simplest organic structures.

20:01.760 --> 20:07.560
So everything has to arise by way of quote unquote evolution.

20:07.560 --> 20:13.120
This is the given, because obviously we live not in a world of particles,

20:13.120 --> 20:21.520
but in a world of something which may conceivably reduce

20:21.520 --> 20:29.600
an aggregate of particles, but it certainly is not what appears to us.

20:29.600 --> 20:39.840
So what I'm trying to say is that if you base yourself on an ontology

20:39.840 --> 20:46.400
of particles, then evolution is an absolute necessity

20:46.400 --> 20:52.360
to go from these particles to the world which we inhabit.

20:52.360 --> 20:56.160
Because the world which we inhabit is more than some of its parts.

20:56.160 --> 21:02.600
It's also one of the things you seem to keep pressing on in this book of yours,

21:02.600 --> 21:08.200
that there is an irreducible hole that you cannot take apart,

21:08.240 --> 21:14.160
you cannot atomize it, and this is also one of the things you stress.

21:14.160 --> 21:23.480
Yes, yes, I do stress this, but the point, Jack, is that

21:23.480 --> 21:29.880
according to the contemporary scientific mindset,

21:29.880 --> 21:34.280
everything does reduce to a sum of parts.

21:34.320 --> 21:38.520
This is what our Weltanschauung insists upon.

21:38.520 --> 21:44.000
Physics by its very modus operandi assumes this much.

21:44.000 --> 21:49.920
The only reason physics can understand an object, whatever it may be,

21:49.920 --> 21:56.600
is that object is a sum of parts, because that's how physics operates.

21:56.600 --> 22:00.520
That's where differential equations come into the picture.

22:00.520 --> 22:09.680
So our contemporary science is predicated upon this assumption

22:09.680 --> 22:16.840
that the world consists of sums of parts.

22:16.840 --> 22:23.880
And now I wanted to point out that it turns out,

22:23.880 --> 22:30.120
and incidentally that's another way of introducing the idea of evolution.

22:30.120 --> 22:31.840
It's the same thing.

22:31.840 --> 22:39.040
If you start with particles, then the world and everything in it

22:39.040 --> 22:42.200
is a result of evolution.

22:42.200 --> 22:45.520
These parts come together to form holes,

22:45.520 --> 22:52.600
and so you get ever more complicated aggregates of particles.

22:52.600 --> 22:58.520
And this is the explanation of the world in which we find ourselves.

22:58.520 --> 23:09.480
But it turns out that this basic premise is untenable.

23:09.480 --> 23:17.240
And that is a direct consequence

23:17.240 --> 23:21.760
over a rigorous mathematical theorem

23:21.760 --> 23:32.560
proved in the year 1998 by an American mathematician named William Demsky.

23:32.560 --> 23:38.080
And what Demsky proved is really very, very simple,

23:38.080 --> 23:44.280
although the proof is not very simple, but the idea is very simple.

23:44.280 --> 23:55.240
Demsky proved that if you have something sufficiently complicated,

23:55.240 --> 24:03.000
then it becomes mathematically impossible to suppose

24:03.000 --> 24:11.880
that this entity came about by chance.

24:11.880 --> 24:21.200
If you have some stochastic random process like tossing a coin,

24:21.200 --> 24:30.760
the likelihood that this will somehow spell out all the volumes

24:30.760 --> 24:35.720
in the Library of Congress in their chronological order

24:35.720 --> 24:41.680
is so small that it is rigorously impossible.

24:41.680 --> 24:50.600
And this is what Demsky proved in this so-called intelligent design theorem,

24:50.600 --> 24:57.800
which was published in a book in Cambridge University Press in 1998.

24:57.800 --> 25:06.640
So what the theorem of Demsky affirms is that

25:06.640 --> 25:13.800
a causality operating in time, which is a causality of physics,

25:13.800 --> 25:21.640
cannot produce what is called complex specified information.

25:21.640 --> 25:26.520
And with this causality, you specifically refer to horizontal causation.

25:26.520 --> 25:29.640
Yes, so horizontal causation.

25:29.640 --> 25:33.760
So when I saw this term for the first time, or this vertical causation,

25:33.760 --> 25:38.080
and I've never heard of it before, immediately I thought,

25:38.080 --> 25:40.080
okay, so what does Wolfgang mean?

25:40.080 --> 25:43.640
Because by that point I had not read your book,

25:43.640 --> 25:49.080
and I can imagine you have on the one hand a cause,

25:49.080 --> 25:52.880
which leads to an effect, and that effect can be another cause.

25:52.880 --> 25:55.760
And we imagine this, at least in the Western world,

25:55.760 --> 25:58.760
because we do not have circular time in our Western thinking.

25:58.760 --> 26:00.560
We have a linear time going,

26:00.560 --> 26:04.320
and it usually is imagined from the left to the right.

26:04.320 --> 26:07.560
So that seems to me the horizontal causation,

26:07.560 --> 26:11.720
but you introduce an idea which is vertical causation,

26:11.720 --> 26:18.480
which might explain some instant annuity.

26:18.480 --> 26:21.960
Sorry, but I just wanted to...

26:21.960 --> 26:24.040
You're absolutely right.

26:24.040 --> 26:29.800
What Demsky's theorem affirms, to put it in my language,

26:29.840 --> 26:32.480
is that horizontal causation,

26:32.480 --> 26:36.280
the causation upon which physics is based,

26:36.280 --> 26:41.680
cannot produce complex specified information.

26:41.680 --> 26:48.000
And since even the simplest forms of life, an amoeba,

26:48.000 --> 26:53.440
as it were, embodies huge quantities

26:53.440 --> 26:57.360
of complex specified information,

26:57.360 --> 27:02.680
it follows from Demsky's theorem that a natural process,

27:02.680 --> 27:05.920
a process that physics can understand,

27:05.920 --> 27:12.160
could not have formed that organic organism, that amoeba.

27:12.160 --> 27:18.640
So the point that I'm making is that, actually,

27:18.640 --> 27:25.600
with Demsky's theorem, evolution, as we normally conceive of it,

27:25.600 --> 27:30.720
has become mathematically impossible.

27:30.720 --> 27:42.720
And the fact that this basic discovery is very much suppressed,

27:42.720 --> 27:52.160
this is not what you will learn at any reputable university.

27:52.160 --> 27:55.920
There are no courses in Harvard or Princeton

27:55.920 --> 27:59.920
that will tell you these things.

27:59.920 --> 28:08.320
It shows that when it comes to Weltanschauung,

28:08.320 --> 28:17.520
the matter is not based on pure simple logic.

28:17.520 --> 28:19.720
I mean, we are human.

28:19.720 --> 28:23.840
Ideology comes into play.

28:23.840 --> 28:34.000
So as a general statement of what I discovered rather early in life,

28:34.000 --> 28:39.960
is that our so-called scientific Weltanschauung,

28:39.960 --> 28:43.440
which entails the idea, for example, of evolution and life

28:43.440 --> 28:48.640
springing from the mental particles, ultimately,

28:48.640 --> 28:55.480
that this is not a scientific fact.

28:55.480 --> 28:57.400
There's no proof of this.

28:57.400 --> 29:02.240
On the contrary, I've just said there are mathematical theorems

29:02.240 --> 29:05.280
that disprove that possibility.

29:05.280 --> 29:11.880
But the point is that our Weltanschauung, which claims to be scientific,

29:11.880 --> 29:21.440
and if you will, objective is, in fact, ideology-driven.

29:21.440 --> 29:23.040
I agree.

29:23.040 --> 29:24.440
Yeah, Brian, go ahead.

29:24.440 --> 29:25.560
I just wanted to add something.

29:25.560 --> 29:28.000
Wolfgang uses the word Weltanschauung, which

29:28.000 --> 29:31.720
is a German word that just means world view

29:31.720 --> 29:33.680
or how one looks out upon the world.

29:33.680 --> 29:37.000
But just going back to your question, Jack,

29:37.000 --> 29:39.080
if I could reintroduce, you had the question

29:39.080 --> 29:42.320
about the Wolfgang's resolution to the quantum enigma.

29:42.320 --> 29:47.880
And Wolfgang, before you came across Dempke's theorem in 1998,

29:47.880 --> 29:50.040
you wrote a book called The Quantum Enigma, Finding

29:50.040 --> 29:56.960
the Hidden Key, in which you pick up on Heisenberg's description

29:56.960 --> 29:59.480
of what quantum reality is.

29:59.480 --> 30:02.000
And this is what leads you down the path to your resolution.

30:02.000 --> 30:06.560
So maybe you could talk about where you picked up from Heisenberg

30:06.560 --> 30:11.520
and how you came to this resolution.

30:11.520 --> 30:12.020
All right.

30:24.600 --> 30:28.200
Quantum theory was discovered in the early decades

30:28.200 --> 30:30.560
of the 20th century.

30:30.560 --> 30:37.400
And very soon after its discovery,

30:37.400 --> 30:45.040
a problem confronted the physicists, which

30:45.040 --> 30:48.520
they were unable to resolve.

30:48.520 --> 30:50.960
And that is the following.

30:50.960 --> 30:55.800
Quantum theory describes a physical system

30:55.800 --> 30:59.400
by a so-called wave function.

30:59.400 --> 31:04.000
And in that wave function description,

31:04.000 --> 31:10.200
the physical systems behave in a very weird way.

31:10.200 --> 31:13.760
Particles, for example, multilocate.

31:13.760 --> 31:21.600
And you are in a realm totally different from the world

31:21.600 --> 31:28.120
as we know it in our daily life.

31:28.120 --> 31:32.920
But when you, for example, set up an experiment

31:32.920 --> 31:40.440
to measure the position of this, say, multi-locating particle,

31:40.440 --> 31:45.160
you find that at the instant of measurement,

31:45.160 --> 31:48.680
the particle ceases to multi-locate

31:48.680 --> 31:56.080
and actually presents itself at some particular location

31:56.080 --> 31:58.920
in space.

31:58.920 --> 32:01.840
And this, of course, is very puzzling.

32:01.840 --> 32:04.920
How does this miracle arise?

32:04.920 --> 32:14.080
That in an instant, a system completely changes

32:14.080 --> 32:20.600
and becomes something that it was not before.

32:20.600 --> 32:24.160
This is called the measurement problem.

32:24.160 --> 32:30.200
And I became very interested in that problem.

32:30.200 --> 32:35.400
It was about 1995, the abouts.

32:35.400 --> 32:44.640
And I finally became convinced that I

32:44.640 --> 32:48.680
see the one and only way to resolve it.

32:48.680 --> 32:53.000
And I wrote a book to that effect on that subject

32:53.000 --> 33:01.480
called the quantum enigma, where I start from the ground up

33:01.480 --> 33:11.480
and develop the idea, ideas, actually two of them,

33:11.480 --> 33:16.480
that are needed to resolve this problem.

33:16.480 --> 33:20.520
And there are two ideas that you need.

33:20.520 --> 33:27.680
The first idea is the fact that the perceptible world, which

33:27.680 --> 33:31.040
is really the world in which we find ourselves,

33:31.040 --> 33:34.880
happens not to be a quantum world.

33:34.880 --> 33:38.400
It happens not to be even just the physical world.

33:38.400 --> 33:42.320
So the world as a physicist conceives of it

33:42.320 --> 33:44.560
is not the full world.

33:44.560 --> 33:45.840
There's more.

33:45.840 --> 33:48.360
And if there were not more, for example,

33:48.360 --> 33:52.960
there could be no perception, there could be no life.

33:52.960 --> 33:58.760
So I made the basic ontological distinction

33:58.760 --> 34:04.280
between a corporeal entity and the physical entity.

34:04.280 --> 34:08.880
Now a corporeal entity is a kind of entity

34:08.880 --> 34:12.720
which we encounter in our normal daily life.

34:13.480 --> 34:18.960
It's something that we perceive as our senses

34:18.960 --> 34:26.720
and something that has a reality, transcending what

34:26.720 --> 34:34.440
the physicist can describe in abstract mathematical terms.

34:34.440 --> 34:40.640
Now every corporeal object X has associated with it

34:40.640 --> 34:44.560
a physical object, call it Sx.

34:44.560 --> 34:48.280
In other words, the physical object

34:48.280 --> 34:56.880
that classical physics deals with are corporeal objects

34:56.880 --> 35:01.280
as conceived by the physicist.

35:01.280 --> 35:05.480
So there's a difference between the corporeal object

35:05.520 --> 35:14.840
X and the object Sx, which is the physicist's conception

35:14.840 --> 35:17.200
of a corporeal object.

35:17.200 --> 35:20.880
I would say that the corporeal object will be not

35:20.880 --> 35:22.560
reducible to each part.

35:22.560 --> 35:27.160
And the physical object S, or at least an abstract object,

35:27.160 --> 35:32.120
will be decomposable into parts the atomistic way.

35:32.160 --> 35:34.160
Yes, you're absolutely right.

35:34.160 --> 35:39.240
Only at this point in the quantum enigma,

35:39.240 --> 35:45.400
I had not yet introduced this idea of irreducible wholeness.

35:45.400 --> 35:50.840
I simply distinguished the object

35:50.840 --> 35:56.800
that we know in daily life through our normal senses

35:56.800 --> 36:00.640
from the corresponding physical object,

36:00.640 --> 36:04.560
which is reduced.

36:04.560 --> 36:08.800
It is limited by the physicist's assumptions.

36:08.800 --> 36:11.480
So you have to distinguish these two objects.

36:11.480 --> 36:12.880
They're not the same.

36:12.880 --> 36:17.360
So there's a distinction between a corporeal object X

36:17.360 --> 36:21.480
and the physicist's concept of that, which

36:21.480 --> 36:24.680
I call the corresponding physical object.

36:24.680 --> 36:27.120
But does its physical object actually exist,

36:27.120 --> 36:29.080
or is it just an abstraction?

36:31.600 --> 36:34.040
The abstraction of the corporeal objects.

36:34.040 --> 36:35.720
It does exist.

36:35.720 --> 36:38.800
I mean, the physicist does not deal with non-entities.

36:38.800 --> 36:40.800
Yes, it has an existence.

36:40.800 --> 36:42.440
The important thing is that you need

36:42.440 --> 36:44.680
to distinguish between the two.

36:44.680 --> 36:46.720
They're not the same thing.

36:46.720 --> 36:50.200
And as long as you don't see that distinction,

36:50.200 --> 36:54.160
you will not be able to solve the measuring problem.

36:54.160 --> 36:57.920
And this is why this measuring problem has been kicked

36:57.920 --> 37:01.800
around by top scientists, top physicists,

37:01.800 --> 37:04.200
for close to 100 years now.

37:04.200 --> 37:11.480
And actually, it has not been solved by these considerations.

37:11.480 --> 37:15.400
Because in fact, it cannot be solved on that basis.

37:15.400 --> 37:18.120
And the reason it cannot be solved on that basis

37:18.120 --> 37:23.360
is that the crux of the matter is this distinction

37:23.400 --> 37:28.320
between the corporeal entity X and the associated physical

37:28.320 --> 37:29.640
entity Sx.

37:29.640 --> 37:32.080
They're not the same.

37:32.080 --> 37:34.480
The corporeal is more.

37:34.480 --> 37:40.000
And it is this more that is the decisive factor

37:40.000 --> 37:44.600
in the measurement problem.

37:44.600 --> 37:47.760
And so I think physicists are still

37:47.760 --> 37:51.280
thinking of the measurement problem.

37:51.320 --> 37:54.360
The fact is that they cannot solve it

37:54.360 --> 37:57.840
on the basis of physics.

37:57.840 --> 38:02.880
So what I showed in this 1995 book, The Quantum Enigma,

38:02.880 --> 38:08.120
is that in a sense, physics is limited.

38:08.120 --> 38:10.600
It doesn't deal with everything.

38:10.600 --> 38:14.640
And it is, in fact, so limited that it

38:14.640 --> 38:20.320
is incapable of recognizing its own limitation.

38:20.320 --> 38:26.360
The fact that the physicist's world is not the entire world,

38:26.360 --> 38:28.400
that's a basic fact.

38:28.400 --> 38:32.720
And unless you understand the basic facts,

38:32.720 --> 38:38.560
you will not be able to correctly understand anything.

38:38.560 --> 38:42.640
But this basic fact is invisible to physics,

38:42.640 --> 38:44.920
by definition, if you will.

38:44.920 --> 38:47.840
Could you say, I was going to ask Wolfgang,

38:47.840 --> 38:53.360
could you say that Sx exists insofar as it participates in X

38:53.360 --> 38:55.120
or partakes of X?

38:55.120 --> 39:01.960
Yes, it derives its being from X.

39:01.960 --> 39:05.520
And this is a major factor.

39:05.520 --> 39:09.920
But this being that the physical object derives

39:09.920 --> 39:15.000
from the corporeal is something entirely invisible

39:15.000 --> 39:17.320
to the physicist.

39:17.320 --> 39:22.880
Because in fact, being as such is invisible to the physicist,

39:22.880 --> 39:26.680
because being is not a sum of parts.

39:26.680 --> 39:33.200
And all the physicists can ever see is sums of parts.

39:33.200 --> 39:36.000
That's why differential equations come into play,

39:36.000 --> 39:42.960
because when you deal with things that do reduce the sum of parts,

39:42.960 --> 39:48.280
these things then are amenable to study

39:48.280 --> 39:52.120
by means of differential equations.

39:52.120 --> 39:55.000
I used to always have trouble with the concept of something

39:55.000 --> 39:57.760
being more than the sum of its parts,

39:57.760 --> 40:02.080
until I heard an example by John Feveki.

40:02.080 --> 40:07.360
He's, I think, a cognitive scientist, not sure.

40:07.360 --> 40:09.840
And he gave the example of the Necker cube,

40:09.880 --> 40:14.280
the two-dimensional drawing of a three-dimensional cube

40:14.280 --> 40:15.640
in a wire frame.

40:15.640 --> 40:19.120
And you can flip that inside and outside.

40:19.120 --> 40:22.560
And he said, well, you have this two-dimensional drawing,

40:22.560 --> 40:24.880
but the three-dimensional projection

40:24.880 --> 40:28.000
you have in your head, that's the thing that is more

40:28.000 --> 40:29.480
than the sum of its parts.

40:29.480 --> 40:33.240
So only until then I kind of understood

40:33.240 --> 40:34.520
what it really meant for something

40:34.520 --> 40:36.360
to be more than the sum of its parts.

40:36.360 --> 40:38.760
It's not something emergent, or there's

40:38.760 --> 40:42.400
something that is not, you can't reduce the three-dimensional

40:42.400 --> 40:45.200
image in your head to the lines on the paper.

40:45.200 --> 40:48.040
And there has to be something more.

40:48.040 --> 40:49.720
Anyway, I just wanted to add that.

40:49.720 --> 40:56.560
Well, this example that John Feveki gave you

40:56.560 --> 40:59.960
is very, very interesting and very fascinating.

40:59.960 --> 41:06.200
But let me point out that it is not necessary to go to something

41:06.200 --> 41:10.880
as high-falutely as this example,

41:10.880 --> 41:16.760
because take, for example, any quality, say, color,

41:16.760 --> 41:19.800
the color red.

41:19.800 --> 41:24.120
The color red, obviously, is not a sum of parts

41:24.120 --> 41:26.960
because it doesn't even have parts.

41:29.800 --> 41:31.640
That's a good one.

41:31.720 --> 41:37.960
It was Aristotle, really, who recognized

41:37.960 --> 41:42.480
the difference between quantities and qualities.

41:42.480 --> 41:46.480
And the point is that qualities are characterized

41:46.480 --> 41:49.400
by the fact that they have no parts.

41:49.640 --> 42:08.920
So the upshot is that physics and our physical sciences deal

42:08.920 --> 42:15.760
with a very limited aspect of reality.

42:15.760 --> 42:20.560
And in fact, this is where its power comes from.

42:20.560 --> 42:27.400
I always like to quote Goethe, who has said so many wise things.

42:27.400 --> 42:32.080
And one of them is, quote, you understand it,

42:32.080 --> 42:35.800
in the BeschrÃ¤nkung zeigt sich der Meister.

42:35.800 --> 42:41.040
In limitation, the master shows himself.

42:41.040 --> 42:45.080
So the point is that physics gains its power

42:45.080 --> 42:48.440
through the enormity of its limitation.

42:48.440 --> 42:50.480
And what is that limitation?

42:50.480 --> 42:56.440
The limitation is that it will concentrate entirely

42:56.440 --> 42:58.760
upon quantities.

42:58.760 --> 43:05.600
The physicist has no eye for qualities.

43:05.600 --> 43:07.440
He sees no color.

43:07.440 --> 43:10.600
He sees nothing but quantities.

43:10.600 --> 43:14.080
And therefore, he sees nothing but sums of parts.

43:14.080 --> 43:17.120
This is an enormous limitation.

43:17.120 --> 43:20.960
And it is the enormity of this limitation

43:20.960 --> 43:25.960
that gives physics its equally enormous power.

43:28.600 --> 43:35.520
So this, if I had any influence upon universities, which I don't,

43:35.520 --> 43:39.440
this is what I would like to convey to the students,

43:39.440 --> 43:42.040
because it makes for wisdom.

43:42.040 --> 43:46.520
It makes for real understanding.

43:46.520 --> 43:54.960
Our scientific Weltanschauung is bought at a cost.

43:54.960 --> 43:59.920
We pay something to get that Weltanschauung.

43:59.920 --> 44:06.080
And what we pay, in other words, what we lose in the process,

44:06.080 --> 44:13.800
is the qualitative side of the world,

44:13.800 --> 44:21.080
which we completely leave out of account

44:21.080 --> 44:23.800
in our physical sciences.

44:27.880 --> 44:35.600
So actually, if you want to be very precise, very rigorous,

44:35.600 --> 44:45.880
you could say that there is no contemporary scientific Weltanschauung

44:45.880 --> 44:52.120
for the simple reason that our sciences are based upon physics.

44:52.120 --> 45:00.640
And the physical world cannot really be looked upon at all.

45:00.640 --> 45:07.440
The only way you can deal with it is through mathematical equations.

45:07.440 --> 45:14.200
And so in order to make a Weltanschauung out of the findings of physics,

45:14.200 --> 45:19.240
we have to add something to that,

45:19.240 --> 45:25.160
which cannot in any way be based upon physics.

45:25.160 --> 45:30.400
So in a sense, our contemporary Weltanschauung is a fake.

45:30.440 --> 45:32.400
It is a fallacy.

45:32.400 --> 45:34.880
It's a contradiction in terms,

45:34.880 --> 45:40.720
because if the world were really what the physicist takes it to be,

45:40.720 --> 45:44.960
that does not give rise to Weltanschauung.

45:44.960 --> 45:49.920
This is nothing that you can tell the non-physicist,

45:49.920 --> 45:53.720
aha, that's what the world is like,

45:53.720 --> 46:00.280
because all that remains basically are equations.

46:00.280 --> 46:06.120
And the non-specialist doesn't understand these equations,

46:06.120 --> 46:11.080
nor does it make any sense to say that in reality,

46:11.080 --> 46:14.520
the world reduces to equations.

46:14.520 --> 46:17.560
This is really nonsense.

46:17.560 --> 46:21.440
And this is why I like the saying of Goethe so much,

46:21.440 --> 46:33.520
because this Goethe's dictum really tells us why the physicist's Weltanschauung

46:33.520 --> 46:36.040
is not a Weltanschauung at all,

46:36.040 --> 46:41.640
unless he added something, an ingredient which is not part of physics,

46:41.640 --> 46:46.640
he couldn't speak to the non-physicist.

46:46.640 --> 46:48.240
Can I quote you from your book?

46:48.240 --> 46:50.920
I just remind me of something you wrote.

46:51.000 --> 46:52.000
Please.

46:52.000 --> 46:53.000
Please.

46:53.000 --> 47:00.200
You said that people today model along and don't even know anymore what is model

47:00.200 --> 47:04.600
and what is fact, and it's something that I find is really a good quote.

47:04.600 --> 47:09.000
It made me chuckle a bit.

47:09.000 --> 47:12.080
I had the same thing when I was younger.

47:12.080 --> 47:16.000
It almost feels like the scientific worldview,

47:16.000 --> 47:19.560
which isn't actually a worldview,

47:19.600 --> 47:22.800
but it pretends to be one, at least.

47:22.800 --> 47:25.120
But it doesn't tell you it is.

47:25.120 --> 47:30.160
I had to find out later that there is a distinction between modeling the world

47:30.160 --> 47:32.800
or describing the world and the world in itself,

47:32.800 --> 47:37.920
and the model of the world is not the same thing as the world.

47:37.920 --> 47:41.960
And I can understand why people get confused, let's say,

47:41.960 --> 47:45.800
and we need people like Wolfgang and other people

47:45.800 --> 47:51.000
to reintroduce this classical idea, actually.

47:51.000 --> 47:53.000
We seem to have forgotten that.

47:53.000 --> 47:57.000
So I just wanted to add that.

47:57.000 --> 48:09.480
Yes, as a result of this dominance of physical science in our time,

48:09.480 --> 48:19.160
our intellectuals have become very, very confused.

48:19.160 --> 48:25.800
And in these days of mass communication,

48:25.800 --> 48:30.040
these ideas remain not only amongst the intellectuals.

48:30.040 --> 48:33.960
It pervades our civilization.

48:33.960 --> 48:36.360
I think nowadays, even in grade school,

48:36.360 --> 48:43.640
we would give more information about atoms and particles and so on.

48:43.640 --> 48:52.920
So we are very, very confused people, seriously confused.

48:52.920 --> 49:01.960
And it, of course, affects our entire civilization profoundly.

49:01.960 --> 49:07.240
I mean, for example, the arts are profoundly affected

49:07.240 --> 49:14.840
by this so-called scientific Weltanschauung,

49:14.840 --> 49:18.760
which is, I have just tried to explain, is really a fake.

49:18.760 --> 49:24.120
It is really a fake.

49:24.120 --> 49:32.360
But these things are not easy to understand intellectually.

49:32.360 --> 49:41.080
It requires certain qualifications, which are apparently quite rare.

49:41.080 --> 49:51.160
And so the confusion remains and, in fact, perpetuates itself.

49:51.160 --> 49:59.080
And it's getting worse and worse.

49:59.080 --> 50:01.960
We are very, very confused people.

50:01.960 --> 50:06.520
And it is affecting our culture as a whole.

50:06.520 --> 50:15.720
And to the extent that one actually sees what is going on,

50:15.720 --> 50:20.360
one cannot but be very worried.

50:21.080 --> 50:29.240
Wolfgang, you introduced a concept as a correlation to horizontal causation,

50:29.240 --> 50:30.520
it's vertical causation.

50:30.520 --> 50:35.880
And you picked up on where Heisenberg said something about quantum particles,

50:35.880 --> 50:38.760
that they're somewhere between being and non-being.

50:38.760 --> 50:41.400
It has such a reminiscent of Aristotelian potentiae.

50:41.400 --> 50:44.360
And this is something you picked up on.

50:44.360 --> 50:46.760
And you said something interesting, you're quoted in your documentary,

50:46.760 --> 50:51.000
saying that no one on either side of the Copenhagen debate

50:51.000 --> 50:53.960
seemed to have realized that it was the role of quantum particles

50:53.960 --> 50:57.160
not to bestow, but to receive being.

50:57.160 --> 51:03.560
And so this plays into your idea of vertical causation,

51:03.560 --> 51:05.640
